description._content: Group portrait of members of Royal Australian Historical Society, taken on excursion to 'cairn' of stones at Linden, known as Caley's Repulse. This image is part of a collection entitled ‘Blue Mountains Excursions', which is available to view on the Royal Australian Historical Society's Historypin Channel. Access the collection at the following link: www.historypin.com/channels/view/id/48441/#|collections/v... Please feel free to comment on this or any of the other images in the collection. If you have more accurate information regarding the location and/or date of the image, we would love to hear from you!
